Information

Further Personal Information

Residence Columbus, OH, USA
Occupation Athlete
Languages English
Higher education Criminology - Ohio State University: Columbus, OH, USA

Sport Specific Information

When and where did you begin this sport? She began fencing at age eight.
Club / Team Ohio State University: Columbus, OH, USA
Name of coach Paul ApSimon [national], CAN
Handedness Right

General Interest

Nicknames Baby Goldie, Lanna (Twitter profile, 02 Mar 2016; ohiostatebuckeyes.com, 16 Mar 2015)
Hobbies Watching television. (Instagram profile, 05 Jul 2018)
Memorable sporting achievement Her first victory at a World Cup event. (ohiostatebuckeyes.com, 16 Mar 2015)
Most influential person in career Her father Brad. (ohiostatebuckeyes.com, 16 Mar 2015)
Hero / Idol Jamaican sprinter Usain Bolt. (ohiostatebuckeyes.com, 16 Mar 2015)
Injuries She broke her heel bone in 2014. (buckeyextra.dispatch.com, 28 Nov 2014)
Superstitions / Rituals / Beliefs She wears the same shirt and shorts to each competition. (ohiostatebuckeyes.com, 16 Mar 2015)
Sporting philosophy / motto "You will never influence the world by trying to fit into it." (Facebook profile, 03 Jun 2018)
Famous relatives Her older sister Brita Goldie has represented Canada in fencing. She competed in a number of World Cup events between 2005 and 2010. (SportsDeskOnline, 25 Jun 2015; canada.com, 24 Jun 2008)
Other information NATIONAL FIRST
In 2010 she became the first female Canadian fencer to win the cadet, junior and senior national titles in the same year. (avenuecalgary.com, 02 Dec 2011)
